WELCOME TO GENIUS' MAY 2019 ALBUM RELEASE CALENDAR!!!



For May 2019 singles releases, visit this page



This page highlights the notable albums, EPs, mixtapes, etc, released in all genres throughout May 2019. Each corresponding annotation lists a tracklist, complete with links to the lyrics, hosted here on Genius. The number to the right of the title serves as a counter of how many songs are up on Genius.

HOW CAN YOU HELP?


Adding projects



If there’s a notable project you think should be listed here, add it! Or add a comment at the bottom of the page if you’re not sure. No self-promotion, please.


Adding lyrics



If you transcribed a song, comment on the album’s annotation and it will be linked into the tracklist


Updating dates



If we have any dates wrong, etc, add a comment at the bottom of the page.

search_results.lyrics:
This Is Your Life Lyrics[Verse 1]
This is your life
Don't let it just happen to you
What's your move?
The deal's on the table in clear view

[Pre-Chorus]
Fists up, your eyes in mine
They don't know how hard you gotta fight

[Chorus]
And I'll tell you what it is
The moment you see it, you want it, take the risk
You're out of your mind and that's alright
Out of your mind, it is what it is or it is not
[Verse 2]
This is your life
Don't let someone else carry you through
What's your move?
You feel like the whole world is watching you

[Pre-Chorus]
Fists up, your eyes in mine
They don't know how hard you gotta fight

[Chorus]
And I'll tell you what it is
The moment you see it, you want it, take the risk
You're out of your mind and that's alright
Out of your mind, it is what it is or it is not
You're out of your mind and that's alright
Out of your mind, it is what it is or it is not

[Post-Chorus]
It is what it is or it is not
It is what it is or it is not

[Outro]
This is your life
This is, this is your life
This is, this is your life
This is, this is your lifeYou might also like1Embed

All I Wanted Lyrics[Chorus]
All I really wanted was you
Play your records all the time
I memorize your every line
All I really wanted was you
Take you for one last ride

[Verse 1]
You're all I need
Don't look at me like that
I know there's something
That you're trying to hold back
Right from the start
You were playing with a broken heart
[Pre-Chorus]
I could feel you in my bones
Don't tell me this love is wrong
Would you be my ride or die?
I know you better than anyone
You're everywhere before you're done

[Chorus]
All I really wanted was you
Play your records all the time
I memorize your every line
